<Link id="l00569" /><CodeLine lineNumber="569"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00570" /><CodeLine lineNumber="570"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Compute the order in which we serialize Frames.  The order does not matter</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00571" /><CodeLine lineNumber="571"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// in terms of correctness, but we still compute it for deserialization</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00572" /><CodeLine lineNumber="572"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// performance.  Specifically, if we serialize frequently used Frames one</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00573" /><CodeLine lineNumber="573"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// after another, we have better cache utilization.  For two Frames that</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00574" /><CodeLine lineNumber="574"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// appear equally frequently, we break a tie by serializing the one that tends</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00575" /><CodeLine lineNumber="575"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// to appear earlier in call stacks.  We implement the tie-breaking mechanism</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00576" /><CodeLine lineNumber="576"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// by computing the sum of indexes within call stacks for each Frame.  If we</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00577" /><CodeLine lineNumber="577"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// still have a tie, then we just resort to compare two FrameIds, which is</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="578"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// just for stability of output.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="579"><Highlight kind="normal">  std::vector&lt;std::pair&lt;memprof::FrameId, const memprof::Frame &#42;&gt;&gt; FrameIdOrder;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="580"><Highlight kind="normal">  FrameIdOrder.reserve(MemProfFrameData.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mapvector/#acf4c09e1f30cdd4e0b5b1b8a236ead34">size</a>());</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><Highlight kind="normal">    FrameIdOrder.emplace&#95;back(Id, &amp;Frame);</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><Highlight kind="normal">                 </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> std::pair&lt;memprof::FrameId, const memprof::Frame &#42;&gt; &amp;R) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><Highlight kind="normal">               </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &amp;SL = FrameHistogram&#91;L.first&#93;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><Highlight kind="normal">               </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &amp;SR = FrameHistogram&#91;R.first&#93;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><Highlight kind="normal">               </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Popular FrameIds should come first.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><Highlight kind="normal">               </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (SL.Count != SR.Count)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><Highlight kind="normal">                 </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> SL.Count &gt; SR.Count;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><Highlight kind="normal">               </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If they are equally popular, then the one that tends to appear</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><Highlight kind="normal">               </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// earlier in call stacks should come first.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><Highlight kind="normal">               </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (SL.PositionSum != SR.PositionSum)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><Highlight kind="normal">                 </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> SL.PositionSum &lt; SR.PositionSum;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><Highlight kind="normal">               </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Compare their FrameIds for sort stability.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><Highlight kind="normal">               </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> L.first &lt; R.first;</Highlight></CodeLine>
